unmarshal

public WorldObject unmarshal(com.thoughtworks.xstream.io.HierarchicalStreamReader reader,
                             com.thoughtworks.xstream.converters.UnmarshallingContext context)

Reads a world object instance from XML. The belongings cannot be completely initialized, thus a later binding mechanism is required. World objects which model is null have to be replaced by the instances having the same ID. This mechanism is implemented in the EntitiesFactory.repairBelongings.

A ConversionException is thrown if a problem arose during the conversion.

Specified by:
unmarshal in interface com.thoughtworks.xstream.converters.Converter

reader - the XStream reader
context - the XStream context
